					     MindSphere
				

























Singapore Digitalization Hub
Siemens partners with Singapore to establish its first fully-integrated Digitalization Hub. Powered by MindSphere – Siemens' cloud-based open IoT operating system, the Hub will drive digitalization in the country on its way to become a Smart Nation.

























MindSphere
The cloud-based, open IoT operating system from Siemens. For the digital transformation of companies regardless of industry or size. Implementable within a very short period of time.























					 This week at Siemens
				





See all news













Jul 19, 2017
Dry before cooking!
During the production process, pasta needs a well-functioning ventilation system to reduce the amount of water in the dough. This ensures the perfect taste.
















Jul 18, 2017
Power despite the calm
Renewable energy sources can be unpredictable, making modern and flexible energy storage solutions all the more important. This is where Fluence comes in – the new company from Siemens and AES.
















Jul 14, 2017
Sheets Ahead
Offices are going paperless, but we’re living in boxes and eating in cardboard restaurants? And why not, because paper is no longer just paper.
















Jul 12, 2017
Better surfing on the train
The train is travelling at high speed, but the sluggish internet trails behind. Not any more: Intelligent layers on train window panes greatly improve signal reception for mobile terminals.
















Jul 06, 2017
Siemens invest $300 million in Walpole, Mass.
Healthcare is changing all over the world. These changes offer great opportunities: The investment in Walpole will create up to 700 new high-tech jobs – and local value.



















